    "Evaluation": {
      "text": ".\nLabs\nCBC, BMP,\nUA\n,\nlactate\nUrine culture, blood cultures\nSome studies have shown up to 66% will have + blood cultures\nImaging\nRenal ultrasound\nWell-defined hypoechoic lesion with thick walls and usually with internal debris\nCT",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "UA",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/UA"
        },
        {
          "text": "lactate",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Lactate"
        },
        {
          "text": "Renal ultrasound",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Renal_ultrasound"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Antibiotics\nBroad spectrum if unclear source\nIf urinary source cover typical urinary pathogens\nCeftriaxone\n1g IV\nPiperacillin-Tazobactam\n4.5 g IV\nIf hematogenous spread considered, cover for MSSA and MRSA\nVancomycin\n15-20mg/kg IV\nPercutaneous drainage\nOpen surgical management if patient fails antibiotics/percutaneous drainage",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
